title: List EDOGE on CarbonSwap
body:
Greetings SUSU power holders, I would like to present to you why myself and many others feel EDOGE deserves a proper listing on the CarbonSwap DEX.

First off by addressing the elephant in the room. It was clear that the launch tokenomics weren't properly thought out. Distribution being the biggest issue followed by liquidity. In it's early stage EDOGE had fell victim to a huge initial rise in price with low liquidity. Attempts were made to stabilize the pool and bring in liquidity. Big wallets were brought together to bring in a better distribution, but a cascading sell-off dragged the price down to a crash. Even the original dev left and is nowhere to be found.
Just so happens that with a mixture of a free market and a little bit of time the two problems have ironed themselves out. One quick look at the distribution we have now and you can see how much it's spread out in comparison pre-dump. Liquidity has also been stable for the past couple weeks staying above $2500. Even with the huge dumps that have been spotted the price impact seems to be very nominal. EDOGE hit it's bottom a while ago and has had consistent growth thereafter despite being in one of the greatest bear markets I've witnessed in crypto. We're at the best possible place we could be right now. That's why we only have one way to look. That way is up.

All the informayonnaise I bring to the table can be validated @
https://info.carbonswap.exchange/
https://explorer.energyweb.org/tokens

As mentioned prior, the dev left. Leaving the project headless. There's no "one" person that is head of the project now. It has become a community token. As such the community has continued to express their desires in getting EDOGE listed on CarbonSwap. Ultimately EDOGE would obtain better exposure if it were listed in the default list. Bringing more awareness to the project could help find more ideas and manpower from the community to give the token utility. At the very least EDOGE could assist in bringing over more publicity and awareness to the Energy Web Chain. Anyone that discovers EWC will surely see EDOGE as it's ranked #9 for holders on the block explorer token list. Sitting at nearly 500.

I'm not going to sit here and pretend that EDOGE deserves a vote because it's some crazy important token to the EWC ecosystem. Because it isn't. It's only a meme token, just like SMUDGE. But I do think it deserves a vote because it's a legit token on a legit chain with a legit community.

Energy Doge for an Energy Web.
https://edoge.xyz/
